-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-04-18T07:09:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/european-stocks-are-little-changed-synthes-soars-on-merger-talks-with-j-j.html
European stocks were little changed
as European Central Bank policy makers said they may further
increase  interest rates . Asian shares swung between gains and
losses, while U.S. futures retreated.  Synthes Inc. surged 11 percent after the Swiss company
confirmed it is holding talks about a possible merger with
 Johnson & Johnson. (JNJ)  Solvay SA rose after BofA Merrill Lynch
Global Research recommended the chemical maker and Lanxess AG
advanced 1.3 percent as Citigroup Inc. said it may have a record
year.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index dropped 0.2 percent to
277.3 at 8:07 a.m. in London, while Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index
